      "writtenOn": "2020-05-19T13:13:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I know that the details of the node counts aren\u0027t super important, as it\u0027s all relative, but even relative to others, this seems odd? The case values are always going to be some kind literal, but the case itself is also counted, so it\u0027s basically 2x number of cases? Maybe that\u0027s fair, given how complex switches are at the lower level?",
