      "writtenOn": "2020-05-19T13:32:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I decided to go with a literal \"number of nodes\" rule everywhere for consistency - so e.g. 1 + 1 is likewise three nodes, one for each of the literals and one for the binary node itself. \"case 1: break;\" being three nodes is just following the same rule.\n\nAs you say, I don\u0027t think the exact numbers are super important, but I think the rules are at least consistent.",
